title: Car crashes into Charnwood Woolworths in Canberra's north - ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation)
text:
Car crashes into Charnwood Woolworths in Canberra's north Posted February 22, 2017 14:49:59 
A car has smashed through the entrance of a supermarket at Charnwood in Canberra's north. 
Police officers and an ambulance were called to the Woolworths store on Charnwood Place at about 11:30am. 
Nobody was injured in crash, understood to have involved an elderly driver who accidentally accelerated into the store. 
The front doors of the supermarket were pushed in, leaving broken glass strewn around the entrance. 
An ACT Policing spokeswoman was unable to provide any details about the driver for privacy reasons, 
Woolworths was contacted for comment.
